<TITLE>Big Dummy's Guide to the Internet - Midget Smileys</TITLE>
<P>Go to the <A HREF="bdg_292.html">previous</A>, <A HREF="bdg_294.html">next</A> section.<P>
<H2><A NAME="SEC296" HREF="bdg_toc.html#SEC296">Midget Smileys</A></H2>
<P>
A lot of these can be typed without noses to make midget smileys.
<P>
<B><CODE>:)</CODE></B>
Midget smiley.
<P>
<B><CODE>:]</CODE></B>
Gleep...a friendly midget smiley who will gladly be your friend.
<P>
<B><CODE>=)</CODE></B>
Variation on a theme...
<P>
<B><CODE>:}</CODE></B>
What should we call these? (what?)
<P>
<B><CODE>:)</CODE></B>
Happy.
<P>
<B><CODE>:&#62;</CODE></B>
What?
<P>
<B><CODE>:@</CODE></B>
What?
<P>
<B><CODE>:D</CODE></B>
Laughter.
<P>
<B><CODE>:I</CODE></B>
Hmmm...
<P>
<B><CODE>:(</CODE></B>
Sad.
<P>
<B><CODE>:[</CODE></B>
Real Downer.
<P>
<B><CODE>:&#60;</CODE></B>
What?
<P>
<B><CODE>:{</CODE></B>
What?
<P>
<B><CODE>:O</CODE></B>
Yelling.
<P>
<B><CODE>:C</CODE></B>
What?
<P>
<B><CODE>:Q</CODE></B>
What?
<P>
<B><CODE>:,(</CODE></B>
Crying.
<P>
<B><CODE>[]</CODE></B>
Hugs and ...
<P>
<B><CODE>:*</CODE></B>
Kisses.
<P>
<B><CODE>|I</CODE></B>
Asleep.
<P>
<B><CODE>^o</CODE></B>
Snoring.
<P>
