<TITLE>Big Dummy's Guide to the Internet - Usenet Smileys</TITLE>
<P>Go to the <A HREF="bdg_294.html">previous</A>, <A HREF="bdg_296.html">next</A> section.<P>
<H2><A NAME="SEC298" HREF="bdg_toc.html#SEC298">Usenet Smileys</A></H2>
<P>
In some Usenet articles you might also find these smileys which form a certain
"dialect" developed and used in this most creative environment.
<P>
<B><CODE>~~:-(</CODE></B>
Net.flame
<P>
<B><CODE>O |-)</CODE></B>
Net.religion
<P>
<B><CODE>8 :-I</CODE></B>
Net.unix-wizards
<P>
<B><CODE>X-(</CODE></B>
Net.suicide
<P>
<B><CODE>E-:-I</CODE></B>
Net.ham-radio
<P>
