<TITLE>Big Dummy's Guide to the Internet - Others</TITLE>
<P>Go to the <A HREF="bdg_304.html">previous</A>, <A HREF="bdg_306.html">next</A> section.<P>
<H3><A NAME="SEC308" HREF="bdg_toc.html#SEC308">FTP'able &#38; Gopher'able Addresses</A></H3>
<B>ftp.eff.org</B>
In directory <TT>`/pub/agitprop'</TT> you'll find the contents of
a disk containing "Literacy Freeware" by Bruce Sterling.
<P>
In directory <TT>`/pub/cud'</TT> you'll find the "Computer underground Digest"
archives.
<P>
<B>gopher.well.sf.ca.us</B>
Gopher this site and browse through the index. It's full of
e-text publications.
<P>
<B>tic.com</B>
In directory <TT>`Bruce Sterling's agitprop/'</TT> you'll find the contents of
the "Literacy Freeware" disk by Bruce Sterling.
<P>
<PRE>
<EM>"And all else is literature."</EM>
--- <B>Paul Verlaine</B>, The Sun, New York
While he was city editor in 1873--1890.
</PRE>
<P>
