<H1>Math 228 -- Discrete Mathematics -- F.E.J. Linton</H1>

<P>
Here is a list of books selecta from which will be distributed
in class as reading material.
<P>
The list is not entirely exhaustive, but it comes close to being
so.
<P>
Garrett Birkhoff &amp; Saunders Mac Lane, <i>A Survey of Modern
Algebra</I>, revised ed., MacMillan, New York, 1953.
<P>
William J. LeVeque, <i>Topics in Number Theory, Vol. I</I>, Addison-Wesley,
Reading (MA), 1956.
<P>
Roger B. Nelsen, <i>Proofs Without Words</I>, MAA, Washington
(D.C.), 1993.
<P>
Ralph N. McKenzie, George F. McNulty, &amp; Walter F. Taylor,
<i>Algebras, Lattices, Varieties, Vol. I</I>, Wadsworth &amp;
Brooks/Cole, Monterey (CA), 1987.
<P>
Robin J. Wilson &amp; John J. Watkins, <i>Graphs: An Introductory
Approach</I>, John Wiley &amp; Sons, New York, 1990. 
