<A NAME="5" HREF="#6"><STRONG>Transitions and DOD Interactions.</STRONG></A><P>

<!Comment: following is an ordered list >
<!Comment: each new item in the list starts with a 'LI'  the left margin >
<!Comment: if you have none to report, then remove the 3 lines below >

<OL>
 <LI>  Peter Freyd was named Director of the Logic and Computation
Laboratory, University of Pennsylvania, Sept. 1993.
<LI> Jim Lipton was appointed assistant professor of computer science at
Wesleyan University. 
<LI> Stacy Finkelstein was awarded a Ph. D. at the University of
Pennsylvania and appointed to a postdoctoral position at McGill
University. 
<LI> We have continued to make use of consulting as a way of bringing
different research groups in relational computing together. This has
included meetings with Oege de Moor and other members of the Oxford
PRG, the Einhoven relational specification group
(Jaap van der Woude), the disjunctive lambda calculus group in Turin
(Ugo de Liguoro), and most recently, consulting support for Dan
Dougherty of Wesleyan University in combinatory logic and rewriting.
We are planning a follow up workshop to the Oxford workshop in
Categories, Relations and Computer Science last summer. Also travel
support has been provided for Michael O'Donnell to carry out research
with Jim Lipton on relational realizability (with reciprocal support
for travel by Lipton from the  University of Chicago).
</OL>

