<A NAME="6" HREF="#7"><STRONG>Software and Hardware Prototypes.</STRONG></A><P>

<!Comment: following is an ordered list >
<!Comment: each new item in the list starts with a 'LI'  the left margin >
<!Comment: if you have none to report, then remove the 3 lines below >

<OL>
<LI> The <TT> Ralog </TT> relational programming language: a
combinatory (variable-free) database language for defining relation
expressions over various relational structures and <i> evaluating
</I> them: a process that combines relational rewriting of relation
expressions  with 
representation of the solution (as a formula over a term algebra) using
(Mal'cev's) quantifier elimination. Briefly discussed in 
<a href="/~lipton/ONR/ralog-intro.dvi"> <i>Intro to Ralog</I></a>
and more in depth in 
<a href="/~lipton/ONR/dist-ilps94.dvi">
<i> ``Combinatory Logic programming'' </I></a>.
</OL>

