<h2>"They that can give up essential liberty to obtain a little temporary
safety deserve neither liberty nor safety."  -- Benjamin Franklin</h2>
<hr><P>

<h2>The Electronic Frontier Foundation</h2>

<p>

The Electronic Frontier Foundation was established to "civilize the 
electronic frontier; to make it useful and beneficial not just to a 
technical elite, but to everyone; and to do this in keeping with our 
society's highest traditions of the free and open flow of information and 
communication." (EFF Mission Statement -- April, 1990)

<p>

In a major effort to inform the general public about the Clipper Chip 
initiative and campaign for needed restrictions to the current proposal, 
the EFF has set up a comprehensive Clipper archive available through their
<a href="http://www.eff.org/">World Wide Web site</a> featuring the following 
collections:

<p>

<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.eff.org/ftp/EFF/Policy/Legislation/cantwell.bill">
Cantwell Bill HR3627</a>
<li><a href="ftp://ftp.eff.org/pub/EFF/Policy/Crypto/">EFF Cryptography Archive</a>
<li><a href="ftp://ftp.eff.org/pub/EFF/Policy/Legislation/">EFF Legislation Archive</a>
<li><a href="ftp://ftp.eff.org/pub/Groups/outposts.faq">List of Cyberliberty Organizations</a>
<li><a href="http://www.eff.org/alerts.html">EFF Alerts</a>
</ul>

<p>
<hr>
<h2>Computer Professionals for Social Responsibility</h2>
<p>
"The mission of Computer Professionals for Social Responsibility (CPSR) is 
to provide the public and policymakers with realistic assessments of the 
power, promise, and problems of information technology. As concerned 
citizens, CPSR members work to direct public attention to critical choices 
concerning the applications of information technology and how those choices 
affect society." (CPSR Brochure)
<p>
After the White House decision to endorse a secret surveillance standard 
for the information highway, CPSR announced a national campaign to oppose 
the government plan. CPSR is the sponsor of an electronic petition urging 
the president to withdraw the Clipper proposal. CPSR has also established a 
comprehensive archive site via the 
<a href="ftp://cpsr.org/">CPSR FTP site</a> or
<a href="gopher://cpsr.org/">CPSR Gopher server</a> featuring the 
following collections:
<p>
<ul>
<li><a href="ftp://cpsr.org/cpsr/privacy/crypto/clipper">CPSR Clipper Archive</a>
<li><a href="ftp://cpsr.org/cpsr/privacy/crypto/">CPSR Cryptography Archive</a>
<li><a href="gopher://gopher.cpsr.org/11/cypherpunks/">CPSR Cypherpunk Archive</a>
</ul><P>
CPSR also put out a special Clipper Edition of their CPSR ALERT bulletin.  You can view it by clicking <a href="cpsr.alert.html">here</a>.

<p><hr><P>

