<TITLE>Claudio Gutierrez Home Page Title</TITLE>
<H1><iMG SRC=""> Chile</H1>

<H5> Chile is a Country whose only interesting features are the poets
	and nature (who wants more?).
<P>
    With respect to nature, more than four thousands kilometers of
mountains and sea separate Chile from the rest of the planet. The longest
and narrowest country of the world, amazes because of its crazy geography.
In this magnificent land of contrasts, varied landscapes embellish with a
wide range of colours this narrow strip of land. Here are found the most
arid desert of the world as well as the immeasurable ice plains of the 
southern glacial fields, and the highest volcano of the planet rises at
short distance of a sea depression of more than 7,000 meters deep. 
Enormous larch trees and araucarias grow in this place, as silent witnesses
of a milenary history.

<P>
  On the other side, poets are a genuine national product. 
(...to be completed)



<H5>
If you would like to know more about Chile, 
the following links could be of interest to you <BR> 
(unfortunately for the english reader, they are mostly in spanish). 
<UL>
<LI>  <A HREF = ""> 
		And&eacute;n</A>: a really nice and complete compilation of 
facts about Chile.
<LI> Newsgroup  <A HREF = "news:soc.culture.chile"> soc.culture.chile </A>:
	a forum of chileans mostly living outside Chile.
<LI> <A HREF = "http://www.presidencia.cl/"> Servidor de la Presidencia </A>: A boring (but complete)
	 compilation of statistics country, its people, government, etc.
	(include of course burocracy of all kinds!)

</UL>
</H5>

<HR>
