<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W30//DTD W3 HTML 2.0//EN"> <HTML> <HEAD>

<TITLE>About KCRW</TITLE>


</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/bg-f.gif">

<CENTER> <A HREF="../m.html"><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="../images/kcrwww.gif"
WIDTH=144 HEIGHT=48 BORDER=0></A></CENTER> 
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<PRE>

</PRE>

<FONT SIZE=+3><B><TT><A HREF="faq.html">KCRW'S FAQ</A></TT></B></FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=+3><B><TT>KCRW AT A GLANCE</TT></B></FONT>


<P> 
<DD><B>KCRW</B>, a community service of <A HREF="http://www.smc.edu">Santa Monica
College</A>,  provides more than 400,000 listeners each week with an eclectic
schedule of
news, locally and nationally produced music, public affairs and radio drama
programs. 
The station broadcasts throughout Los Angeles and Orange Counties on its primary
frequency 89.9 FM, and provides service to the greater Palm Springs area at 89.3
FM on
KCRY/Indio-Palm Springs, and Ventura and Santa Barbara Counties at 89.1 FM on
KCRU/Oxnard-Ventura.  Translators carry the signals to Antelope Valley at 88.1
FM,
Ridgecrest at 107.1 FM, Santa Paula-Moorpark at 102.3 FM, Ojai at 102.1 FM, and
Banning
and the Yucca Valley areas at 90.9 FM.  As a member-supported, non-commercial
station,
70% of KCRW's operating budget comes from its 45,000 subscribers.
<P>
<FONT SIZE=+3><B><TT>KCRW Programming...</TT></B></FONT><BR>
<P>
<DD>"KCRW's programming reflects the diversity of the community it serves.  KCRW
airs more
National Public Radio news than any station in Southern California and is
considered the
flagship station for the network.  In recent years, the station's cultural and
public
affairs programs have won The George Foster Peabody Award, Ohio State Awards, the
Cindy,
the Major Armstrong, The Radio and Television News Directors Association and
Corporation
for Public Broadcasting Awards.  The station was twice named "Nation's Best
Non-Commercial Station" at College Media Journal's New Music Awards, and in 1994,
was the
first public radio station ever to be honored with a Crystal Eagle Award from the
Coro
Foundation for meritorious community service.  KCRW broadcasts more radio drama
than any
station in the country, with productions from our own studios, NPR and the BBC. 
Named
"Best Bit of Everything" radio station by Details Magazine, KCRW's innovative and
acclaimed programming has been recognized with significant press coverage in Los
Angeles
and around the country and the world."
<P>

<FONT SIZE=+3><B><TT>News:</TT></B></FONT><BR>                  "Which Way, L.A.?"
with Warren Olney; NPR's Morning
Edition, All Things                             Considered; Marketplace; Monitor Radio; The
California Capitol Report; plus locally                                 produced interview, talk
and public affairs
shows and specials"
<P>
<FONT SIZE=+3><B><TT>Music:</TT></B></FONT><BR>                         "The station"s
eclectic mix combines world beat, pop,
jazz, rap, hip-hop,                             reggae, African, new wave, classical and new
music with numerous
in-studio                               interviews and live in-studio performances"
<P>
<FONT SIZE=+3><B><TT>Radio Drama:</TT></B></FONT><BR>                   "The best of
BBC"s comedies, dramas and literary adaptations
plus innovative                                 new American productions by the all-star L.A.
Theatre Works Company,
the                             Met Theatre, the Mark Taper Forum, as well as
collaborations with                             independent producers, NPR and
BBC Radio Drama"
<P>
<FONT SIZE=+3><B><TT>Arts/Culture:</TT></B></FONT><BR>                  "The Politics
of Culture and nightly arts and lifestyle reviews highlight
                                KCRW"s locally produced programs"
<P>
<FONT SIZE=+3><B><TT>Audience:  </TT></B></FONT><BR>            
<UL>
        <LI>75% of KCRW listeners are between 25 and 49 years of age 
        <LI>61% are professional, managerial, technical or administrative 
        <LI>32% are urban, upscale professionals with few children 
        <LI>32% are young, mobile, urban and single with few children
</UL>
<P>
<CENTER> <A HREF="../m.html"><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="../images/kcrwww.gif"
WIDTH=144 HEIGHT=48 BORDER=0></A></CENTER> 








</BLOCKQUOTE> </BODY> </HTML>
