<HTML>
<HEAD>

<TITLE>KCRW BOOKWORM</TITLE>


</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../images/bg-c.gif">
<IMG SRC="../images/lastsigh.jpg" ALIGN = RIGHT WIDTH = 102 HEIGHT = 159><A HREF="index.html"><IMG ALIGN=left SRC="../images/12.gif"  WIDTH=96 HEIGHT=96
BORDER=0></A><A HREF="index.html"><BR CLEAR=LEFT><IMG ALIGN=left SRC="../images/11.gif"  WIDTH=96 HEIGHT=96
BORDER=0></A><FONT SIZE=+3><TT><B>SALMAN RUSHDIE</B></TT></FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=-1>KCRWWW SPECIAL PROGRAMMING</FONT>

<BR CLEAR=LEFT>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
Salman Rushdie's novel, <I>The Satanic Verses</I>, has been banned in eleven countries around the world, and the author still lives in the shadow of the death sentence, the <I>fatwa</I>,  issued by Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini in 1989.  Both the Italian and Japanese translators of his book were murdered.<P>
<IMG SRC = "../images/salman.jpg" WIDTH = 108 HEIGHT = 156 ALIGN = LEFT BORDER = 1 HSPACE = 4>KCRWWW presents two programs featuring Rushdie to Internet users <B>worldwide</B>--an interview from <A HREF="bookworm.html">Bookworm</A> with Michael Silverblatt, and Rushdie's first public appearance since the fatwa was issued in 1989.  You can listen to the programs using <A HREF = "http://www.realaudio.com">Real Audio</A> or read printed transcripts.
<P>
Please e-mail us at <A HREF="mailto:webprod@kcrw.org">webprod@kcrw.org</A> with the country where you're reading this, and if you like, comments about the program.  We'll compile it into a guestbook which will be available here.

<P>

<A HREF="http://www.kcrw.org/ra/bwrushdien.ram"><IMG
ALIGN=left SRC="../images/ra2.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=5 VSPACE=5
WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36></A><A HREF="http://www.kcrw.org/ra/bwrushdie.ram"><IMG
ALIGN=left SRC="../images/ra.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=5 VSPACE=5
WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36></A><DL><FONT SIZE = +1><A HREF = "bookworm.html">Bookworm</A> host <B>Michael Silverblatt</B> talks with Salman Rushdie about his life and his new book <I>The Moor's Last Sigh</I>.</FONT>
</DL>
<BLOCKQUOTE>Read a transcript of the interview: <A HREF = "srtransp1.html">Part One</A> and <A HREF="srtransp2.html">Part Two</A>.</BLOCKQUOTE>
<BR CLEAR = LEFT>
<IMG
ALIGN=left SRC="../images/spacer.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=5 VSPACE=5
WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36><A HREF="http://www.kcrw.org/ra/rushdie.ram"><IMG
ALIGN=left SRC="../images/ra.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=5 VSPACE=5
WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36></A><DL><FONT SIZE = +1>Salman Rushdie's speaks at a writers' conference held in London's  Westminster Church in September of 1995. Mr. Rushdie talks, answers questions from the audience, and reads from his latest novel, <I>The Moor's Last Sigh.</I>  Produced by KCRW.</FONT>
</DL>
<BLOCKQUOTE></BLOCKQUOTE>








<P><HR WIDTH = 15%><P>
KCRWWW's audio files are in the RealAudio format for listening convenience. In

order to use RealAudio you need the free <A HREF="http://www.realaudio.com">REAL

AUDIO PLAYER</A> from Progressive Networks.  If you have a 28.8 or better connection, and a fast processor, we recommend Real Audio 2.0.
