<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML 3.0//EN" "html.dtd"><HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Left, Right, & Center</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR = "#669999"><CENTER><IMG SRC = "../images/lrcanim.gif" WIDTH = 576 HEIGHT = 96><BR><BLOCKQUOTE><FONT SIZE = +2><TT><B>News Analysis from Commentators on the Left, the Right, and the Center with Genevieve Wood, Robert Scheer, Matt Miller, and Arianna Huffington.</B></TT></FONT><P><B><TT>AIRS WEDNESDAY, 2 - 2:30 PM</TT></B><P><A HREF = "http://www.kcrw.org/ra/lr70129.ram"><IMG SRC = "../images/ra.gif" WIDTH = 25 HEIGHT = 36 BORDER = 0 HSPACE = 5 ALIGN = ABSMIDDLE></A><FONT SIZE = +1><TT><B>Listen to Left, Right & Center</B></TT></FONT></BLOCKQUOTE></CENTER><BLOCKQUOTE><FONT SIZE = +2><TT><B>About the Hosts:</B></TT></FONT><P><BLOCKQUOTE><B>Arianna Huffington</B> is a Senior Fellow of the Progress and Freedom Foundation, chair of the Center for Effective Compassion, a nationally syndicated columnist, and the author of six books, including, most recently, <I>The Fourth Instinct</I>.  She developed and hosted her own live talk show, "Critical Mass," which focused on such themes as renewing values and revitalizing communities, and which aired on National Empowerment Television from December 1993 until December 1994.  She's currently developing, in conjunction with comedian/satirist (and KCRW programmer) Harry Shearer, "Eat the Press,"  a new show which takes a satirical look at the media's coverage of news.<P><B>Matthew Miller</B> is economics editor of the <I>New Republic</I>, a contributor to <I>Time</I> magazine, and a regular commentator for National Public Radio.  His writing has appeared in the <I>Washington Post</I>, the <I>New York Times</I>, the <I>Wall Street Journal</I>, the <I>Los Angeles Times</I>, the <I>New Yorker</I>, and many regional newspapers.  He has provided policy and political analysis on programs such as Nightline, 20/20, CNN, C-SPAN, Charlie Rose, and the Nightly Business Report.<P><B>Robert Scheer</B> teaches in the Communications Department at UCLA and is a Contributing Editor and Columnist for the <I>Los Angeles Times</I>; his writing has also appeared in the <I>Washington Post</I>, the <I>San Francisco Examiner</I>, <I>Esquire</I>, and <I>Premiere</I> among others.  His interviewees have included Richard Nixon, Jimmy Carter, Jerry Brown, Ronald Reagan, George Bush, and Bill Clinton.  He has authored five books including <I>Thinking Tuna Fish</I>, <I>Talking Death</I> and <I>With Enough Shovels: Reagan, Bush, and Nuclear War</I></BLOCKQUOTE><P>For<FONT SIZE = +1> tapes of the show</font> (sorry, no transcripts), call 310.450.5183.  Tapes are $15.00 each, order with Visa, MasterCard or American Express.  If by check, send payment to KCRW 1900 Pico Blvd, Santa Monica, CA 90405.  Make checks payable to KCRW and please be sure to include the date and/or subject of the broadcast.</BLOCKQUOTE><br><PRE></PRE> <CENTER> <A HREF="../m.html"><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="../images/kcrwww.gif"WIDTH=144HEIGHT=48 BORDER=0></A> </CENTER></BODY></HTML>
