<H1><TT><B><FONT SIZE=+3>Live Performances & Interviews</FONT></TT></B></H1>
<A HREF= "upcoming.html">Upcoming Schedule</A> for <A HREF= "mbehome.html">Morning Becomes Eclectic</A></I><P>
Listen to KCRW Performances on RealAudio's <A HREF = "http://www.liveconcerts.com/harddrive/kcrw/">LiveConcerts.com</A>.<P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>KCRWWW's audio files are in the RealAudio format for listening convenience. In order to use RealAudio you need the free <A HREF="http://www.realaudio.com">REALAUDIO PLAYER</A> from Progressive Networks.
</CENTER>
<P>
<HR>
<BR>
Our internet content is produced using <A HREF="http://www.sfoundry.com">Sonic Foundry's</A>  <I>Soundforge</I> audio software.</P>
<P>
We are currently in the process of upgrading our software to bring you our live performances in stereo.  Please bear with us as we make these changes, and we will update our performance schedule as soon as possible.</P>

<!--Begin Copy-->
<BLOCKQUOTE><A HREF="http://www.liveconcerts.com/harddrive/kcrw/"><IMG ALIGN=left SRC="../images/ra2.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=5 WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36></A><A HREF="http://www.liveconcerts.com/harddrive/kcrw/"><IMG ALIGN=left SRC="../images/ra.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=10 VSPACE=5 WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36></A><DL>
<!--MBE Description begins here-->
 Tom Schnabel to host, and we welcome the return of <B>Madeline Peyroux</B>, a jazz / blues singer whose sultry voice bears an uncanny resemblance to Billie Holiday. Her debut album entitled Dreamland' received much critical claim and she will be performing a mixture of original material reflecting her musical loves - Edith Piaf, Billie  Holiday, Patsy Cline and Fats Waller amongst others. Friday,  January 23, 1997.
<!--MBE Description ends here-->
</DL></BLOCKQUOTE><BR CLEAR=LEFT>
<!--End Copy-->


<!--Begin Copy-->
<BLOCKQUOTE><A HREF="http://www.liveconcerts.com/harddrive/kcrw/"><IMG ALIGN=left SRC="../images/ra2.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=5 WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36></A><A HREF="http://www.liveconcerts.com/harddrive/kcrw/"><IMG ALIGN=left SRC="../images/ra.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=10 VSPACE=5 WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36></A><DL>
<!--MBE Description begins here-->
 Tom Schnabel will be hosting in Chris' absence and is joined by Kronos Quartet's founder <B> David Harrington</B>, in town for performances at the  Irvine Barclay Theatre and the Veterans Wadsworth Theatre.  David will guest d.j in the 10 o'clock hour and as always we look forward to hearing his faves of the moment.   Wednesday,  January 22, 1997.
<!--MBE Description ends here-->
</DL></BLOCKQUOTE><BR CLEAR=LEFT>
<!--End Copy-->

<!--Begin Copy-->
<BLOCKQUOTE><A HREF="http://www.liveconcerts.com/harddrive/kcrw/"><IMG ALIGN=left SRC="../images/ra2.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=5 WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36></A><A HREF="http://www.liveconcerts.com/harddrive/kcrw/"><IMG ALIGN=left SRC="../images/ra.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=10 VSPACE=5 WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36></A><DL>
<!--MBE Description begins here-->
 Composer <B>Gabriel Yared</B>, a 1997 Golden globe nominee for his to the outstanding film 'The English Patient', will join us for the morning after the night before (referring to the Golden Globe Awards) and we liik forward to talking to him about this score as well as those to 'Betty Blue', V'Vincent & Theo' and many others.  Monday,  January 20, 1997.
<!--MBE Description ends here-->
</DL></BLOCKQUOTE><BR CLEAR=LEFT>
<!--End Copy-->


<!--Begin Copy-->
<BLOCKQUOTE><A HREF="http://www.liveconcerts.com/harddrive/kcrw/"><IMG ALIGN=left SRC="../images/ra2.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=5 WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36></A><A HREF="http://www.liveconcerts.com/harddrive/kcrw/"><IMG ALIGN=left SRC="../images/ra.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=10 VSPACE=5 WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36></A><DL>
<!--MBE Description begins here-->
Actor <B>Billy Bob Thornton</B>  has received enormous critical acclaim for his 1996 directorial debut  Sling  Blade' (which he also wrote and starred in) which features a haunting score by Daniel Lanois.  He has just been offered a role in the upcoming film Primary Colours' and we look forward to hearing about his future actor/director plans.  Monday,  January 21, 1997.
<!--MBE Description ends here-->
</DL></BLOCKQUOTE><BR CLEAR=LEFT>
<!--End Copy-->

<!--Begin Copy-->
<BLOCKQUOTE><A HREF="http://www.liveconcerts.com/harddrive/kcrw/"><IMG ALIGN=left SRC="../images/ra2.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=5 WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36></A><A HREF="http://www.liveconcerts.com/harddrive/kcrw/"><IMG ALIGN=left SRC="../images/ra.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=10 VSPACE=5 WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36></A><DL>
<!--MBE Description begins here-->
Composer and guitarist <B>Michael Brook</B> has composed the score to <B>Kevin Spacey's</B> directorial debut entitled "Albino Alligator" (due for release this week) starring Gary Sinise, Matt Dillon, Joe Mantenega and Faye Dunaway. Kevin and Michael join us in the studio and we look forward to hearing about the film (did Kevin really lose the negative of the film in an airport?!) and the collaboration between the composer and director.Aired Wednesday, January 15, 1997.
<!--MBE Description ends here-->
</DL></BLOCKQUOTE><BR CLEAR=LEFT>
<!--End Copy-->

<!--Begin Copy-->
<BLOCKQUOTE><A HREF="http://www.liveconcerts.com/harddrive/kcrw/"><IMG ALIGN=left SRC="../images/ra2.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=5 WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36></A><A HREF="http://www.liveconcerts.com/harddrive/kcrw/"><IMG ALIGN=left SRC="../images/ra.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=10 VSPACE=5 WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36></A><DL>
<!--MBE Description begins here-->
Screen writer and director, <B>Anthony Minghella</B>, comes in for a live interview with Chris Douridas to talk about his latest film project, "The English Patient." Aired Monday, January 13, 1997.
<!--MBE Description ends here-->
</DL></BLOCKQUOTE><BR CLEAR=LEFT>
<!--End Copy-->

<!--Begin Copy-->
<BLOCKQUOTE><A HREF="http://www.liveconcerts.com/harddrive/kcrw/"><IMG ALIGN=left SRC="../images/ra2.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=5 WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36></A><A HREF="http://www.liveconcerts.com/harddrive/kcrw/"><IMG ALIGN=left SRC="../images/ra.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=10 VSPACE=5 WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36></A><DL>
<!--MBE Description begins here-->
Like a middle-American version of the
Tindersticks Lincoln, Nebraska's <B>Lullaby for the Working Class</B> stop into the studio to play some live tracks from their latest release on Bar None Records, "Blanket Warm."Aired Friday, January 10, 1997.
<!--MBE Description ends here-->
</DL></BLOCKQUOTE><BR CLEAR=LEFT>
<!--End Copy-->

<!--Begin Copy-->
<BLOCKQUOTE><A HREF="http://www.liveconcerts.com/harddrive/kcrw/"><IMG ALIGN=left SRC="../images/ra2.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=5 WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36></A><A HREF="http://www.liveconcerts.com/harddrive/kcrw/"><IMG ALIGN=left SRC="../images/ra.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=10 VSPACE=5 WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36></A><DL>
<!--MBE Description begins here-->
Santa Barbara based singer/songwriter <B>Jennifer Terran</B> has produced her own CD entitled 'Cruel', beautifully showcasing her distinctive voice and her writing abilities. Aired Thursday, January 9, 1997.
<!--MBE Description ends here-->
</DL></BLOCKQUOTE><BR CLEAR=LEFT>
<!--End Copy-->

<BLOCKQUOTE><A HREF="http://www.liveconcerts.com/harddrive/kcrw/"><IMG ALIGN=left SRC="../images/ra2.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=5 WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36></A><A HREF="http://www.liveconcerts.com/harddrive/kcrw/"><IMG ALIGN=left SRC="../images/ra.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=10 VSPACE=5 WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36></A><DL>Chris will be back in the saddle to
welcome Candian singer/songwriter <B>Bruce Cockburn</B>(Co-burn) to perform material from his forthcoming CD (just in case you are counting it will be his 23rd album!) 'The Charity of Night'. Aired Monday, January 6, 1997.</DL></BLOCKQUOTE><BR CLEAR=LEFT>

