<B>Lido Book Shoppe</B>, is the independent Newport Beach bookstore that specializes in nautical books and magazines, literature, travel and foreign magazines and newspapers. <B>Lido</B> also carries a large selection of books and magazines on the film industry.  10% discount on all books. 3424 Via Oporto, Newport Beach (714) 675-9595
<P>
<B>Midnight Special</B> is a social and cultural independent bookstore presenting books and ideas to change the world. Their diverse calendar of events features writers such as National Book Award winner author Victor Martinez, (Parrot in the Oven), and international authors, including Argentine novelist Alicia Kozameh, (Steps Underwater), a stunning account of her experience as a political prisoner. 10% off all books. 1318 Third Street Promenade, Santa Monica. (310) 393-2923
<P>
<B>Rizzoli Bookstore & Art Boutique</B> presents books on art, architectures and design in an elegant surrounding, plus an eclectic selection of music and gifts. 10% discount. Locations in Beverly Hills, Pasadena, Santa Monica and South Coast Plaza. 
<P>
<B>Sisterhood Bookstore</B> is celebrating 25 years as the site for a unique collection of books and crafts by and about women, and as a vital hub for women's culture and community in Los Angeles. 10% discount on all books except text and sale books. 1351 Westwood Blvd, West L.A. (310) 477-7300
<P>
<B>Small World Books</B> is a fine literary store on Venice Beach, which strongly emphasizes fiction, poetry and biography, with a well-read staff that will find the perfect book for you.  The large mystery annex includes </I>noir</I> and vampire literature. 10% discount.  Ocean Front Walk, between Horizon and Market Streets, Venice (310) 399-2360
<P>
<B>Storyopolis Bookstore and Art Gallery</B> specializes in showcasing original art and books by storybook illustrators, with art openings and book signings held monthly.  They also host children's craft and story hour every Saturday morning. 10% off all books. 116 N. Robertson Blvd., between Alden & Beverly (310) 358-2500
<P>
<B>Traveler's Bookcase</B> is a "must visit" for any traveler, with more than 14,000 books and maps, so you can plan the perfect trip.  It's the place to go for all your travel information needs.  10% off on all books, maps and accessories. 8375 West Third St. near La Cienega, Los Angeles (213) 655-0575
<P>
<B>Ventura Bookstore</B>, located in historic Downtown Ventura since 1938, has a fine selection of books on all subjects.  Pore through poetry, find fun fiction, linger in the lit section, meander through mysteries.  Seven days a week, the knowledgeable staff of readers will help you choose a book for yourself or a gift for mom or cousin Vinnie.   10% off on books in stock.  522 E. Main St., Ventura.  (805) 643-4069

<P>
<FONT SIZE= +2><B>Museums</B></FONT> <BR>
<P>
<B>Autry Museum of Western Heritage</B> pays homage to the American west, from its Native American roots to its pioneering past and the romance created by Hollywood.  Whether it's the art of Frederick Remington or N.C, Wyeth, the tools and clothing of many cultures, or the costumes and props of film and TV, the whole family will enjoy this captivating exploration of the West's legacy.  20% off admission, $10 off Family/Dual membership. Griffith Park, across from L.A. Zoo (213) 667-2000
<P>
<B>Bowers Museum</B> presents permanent exhibitions of culture, art and California history, world-class changing exhibitions, a gourmet restaurant, stylish store and the children's center <I>Kidseum</I> make the Bowers a "must-see" museum.  One free admission with each adult admission purchased.  Also valid at <I>Kidseum</I>. 2002 N. Main St. at 20th, Santa Ana  (714) 567-3600
<P>
<B>Craft and Folk Art Museum</B> was founded in 1973 as a private, non-profit institution organized to foster aesthetic and cultural understanding. <B>CAFAM's</B> exhibitions and programming focus on folk art, the embellishment of everyday objects used by world cultures, on contemporary crafts and design.  25% off general admission; 10% off shop purchases. 5800 Wilshire Blvd, east of Fairfax, Los Angeles. (213) 937-5544
<P>
<B>Museum of Television & Radio</B> Experience the whole museum.  Attend screenings at the John H. Mitchell Theatre, select from the collection of over 75,000 radio and television programs to view or listen to at an individual console, and attend seminars with performers, directors, writers and producers from your favorite programs.  10% off any new membership. 465 N. Beverly Dr, Beverly Hills (310) 786-1066
<P>
<B>Museum of Tolerance</B> has received worldwide critical acclaim for its captivating and mind-opening presentation of events that have shaped the world as we know it. Through unique interactive exhibits, the high tech, hands-on museum focuses on the dynamics of racism and prejudice in America, and the history of the Holocaust, the ultimate example of man's inhumanity to man. 10% off adult admissions. 9786 Pico Blvd. at Roxbury Dr., Los Angeles. (310) 553-8403
<P>
<B>Pacific Asia Museum</B> is the only museum in the Southwest solely dedicated the presentation, preservation and promotion of the art and culture of Asia and the Pacific.  Features include Chinese carved jade, Japanese painting, Tibetan thankas, the historic Nicholson Treasure house, Chinese garden and coy pond, as well as items from throughout Asia and the Pacific Islands. Two-for-one adult admissions. 46 N. Los Robles Ave. at Colorado, Pasadena. (818) 449-2742
<P>
<B>Palm Springs Desert Museum</B> is an oasis of 105,000 square feet, devoted to art, natural science and the performing arts.  Two-for-one museum admission. 101 Museum Dr., Palm Springs. (619) 325-0189
<P>
<B>Southwest Museum</B> is a living, vibrant cultural institution, entrusted with the responsibility for caring for one of the most significant and extensive collections of Native American art and artifacts in existence. The museum is a major non-profit educational center which presents exhibitions and programming for families, teachers, scholars and collectors.  Two-for-one admission. $10 off any membership. 234 Museum Drive, Los Angeles.  (213) 221-2164
<P>
<B>UCLA/Armand Hammer Museum</B>, in the heart of Westwood Village, serves as a meeting place and showcase for the arts. In addition to a diverse schedule of historical and contemporary art exhibitions organized by UCLA or other major institutions, the museum also presents music, dance, poetry, video, gallery talks, symposia and docent tours for people of all ages.  Two-for-one admission.  50% discount on Active membership.  10899 Wilshire Blvd, Westwood. (310) 443-7000


<P>
<A NAME="venue"></A><FONT SIZE= +2><B>Entertainment
Venues</B></FONT> <BR>
<P>
<I>  You must purchase tickets through the box offices (by phone or in person) and give your KCRW
member number.  All tickets are subject to availability.</I>
<P>
<B>Ahmanson Theatre</B>, currently celebrating its 30th season, presents a wide variety of dramas, comedies, premieres and classical revivals.  Its unique state-of-the-art theater allows for adjustments in the size of the house to accommodate a wide variety of plays, from the intimate to the spectacular. 50% off tickets to Apr 22-May 4 performances of Ferenc Molnar's "The Play's the Thing".  Call (213) 628-2772 and ask for code "KCR".
<P>
<B>Harriet and Charles Luckman Fine Arts Complex</B> brings the arts, in their most creative forms, to Southern California.  The complex, comprised of a theatre, fine arts gallery and street of the arts, is located on the campus of Cal State LA, at the junction of the San Bernardino and Long Beach Freeways. Two-for-one tickets on selected performances. (213) 343-6610
<P>
<B>Irvine Barclay Theatre</B> has one of the most diverse rosters of top-notch entertainment in the area.  No matter what your tastes, you'll find something to delight you -- established stars and emerging new talent, familiar classic and cutting-edge performances, world cultures and children's favorites all in one place. 10% discount on selected performances. (714) 854-4646
<P>
<B>L.A. Opera</B> presents grand opera, from the best loved operas to new 20th century works.  20% off weeknight performances of "The Return of Ulysses".  Call (213) 972-8001
<P>
<B>L.A. Theatre Works</B> is a 20-year old non-profit arts, organization, that is committed to bringing distinguished acting talent together with the world's finest dramatic literature, all in the quest for the most exciting contemporary theater. 20% off individual tickets. (310) 827-0889 or (800) 708-8863
<P>
<B>Laguna Playhouse</B>, the West Coast's oldest theater company, is now one of the region's hottest professional venues, with frequent critics choice designations and packed houses.  Two-for-one tickets on selected performances. (714) 494-8021
<P>
<B>Los Angeles Philharmonic</B> is one of the world's great orchestras, and its Music Director Esa-Pekka Salonen is one of the world's leading conductors.  October through May, the orchestra is in residence at the Music Center. Its summer home is the Hollywood Bowl, one of the world's largest natural amphitheaters, which presents a nightly succession of popular programs in an informal ambiance of picnics and fellowship under a canopy of stars.  20% off selected performances.  In-person only. (213) 850-2000
<P>
<B>Mark Taper Forum</B>, currently celebrating its 30th anniversary season, continues its tradition of presenting world, American and west coast premieres as well as award winning contemporary works.  The intimate 750-seat theater sits at the heart of the Music Center.   50% off tickets to March 2-16 performances of Athol Fugard's "Valley Song". Call (213) 628-2772 and ask for code "KCR".
<P>
<B>Old Globe Theatre</B>, San Diego's Tony Award-winning theatre, offers top-notch performances of Shakespeare, world premiere plays, and musicals featuring the hottest talents in entertainment today.  10% off selected Sun.-Thur. performances; up to 18% off season subscriptions.  Balboa Park. For tickets, (619) 235-2255; subscriptions, (619) 235-2250
<P>
<B>Opera Pacific</B>, one of the nation's top 15 opera companies, presents grand opera at the Orange County Performing Arts Center in Costa Mesa.  With a roster of international artists on stage, each production is a musical work of art.  English surtitles are projected above the stage, much like the subtitles in foreign films, so you'll be able to enjoy every plot twist, even if you're a newcomer to opera. 10% off tickets to selected performances. (800) 346-7372
<P>
<B>Philharmonic Society of Orange County</B> presents the best in classical music from around the globe, plus jazz and world music at concert halls throughout Orange County. 15% off selected performances. (714) 553-2422
<P>
<B>South Coast Repertory</B>, in its 33rd season, is Orange County's only Tony award-winning professional repertory theatre, presenting world-class plays on two state-of-the-art stages.  From classics to contemporary works, <B>SCR's</B> innovative productions have been lauded by critics, artists and audiences alike. Two-for-one tickets on selected performances, Tues., Wed. & Thur. during first 3 weeks of each new production. (714) 957-4033
<P>
<B>UCLA Center for the Performing Arts</B> In a world of entertainment choices, you'll find the best of the live performing arts is at the <B>UCLA Center for the Performing Arts</B>.  10% off selected performances. (310) 825-2101
<P>
<B>William Hall Master Chorale</B> has received critical acclaim both locally and internationally for its diversity and quality of programming.  A resident performing group at the Orange County Performing Arts Center, the <B>Chorale</B> presents an exhilarating year of music that includes romantic melodies for Valentine's Day, the inspiration of great sacred choruses and spirituals, and an evening of music from favorite Broadway shows.  25% off selected performances. (714) 556-6262. 

<P>
<FONT SIZE= +2><B>Miscellaneous</B></FONT> <BR>
<P>
<B>Luna Park</B> 15% on food and beverage in restaurant with prior reservation. 665 N. Robertson Blvd. (310) 652-0611 
<P>
<B>Vidiots</B> dares to be different, with a great selection of classic international films, underground cult masterpieces and the best in documentaries, plus in-store appearances by independent filmmakers and performance artists.  $10 off annual or lifetime membership. 302 Pico Blvd., Santa Monica. (310 392-8508
<P>
<B>Wild Oats Community Markets</B> are Southern California's natural foods markets, with a full line of natural and organic groceries, produce, meats, supplements and body care.  Each market has a full-service deli and fresh juice and java bar. 10% off all purchases. Locations in West Los Angeles, Santa Monica, West Hollywood, Pasadena and Mission Viejo.
<P>


