<head>
<title>SATURDAY'S PAGE</title>
</head>
<body  bgcolor=000000 text=ff0000>
<pre>


<p>
<center><h2>Shortwave</h2></center>
<center><img src="/images/swzap.jpg" WIDTH = 287 HEIGHT = 25"></center>
<p>
<center><img src="/images/swk.gif" WIDTH = 148 HEIGHT = 43></center>
<center><h3>89.9 fm<h3></center>
<center><h3>Mondays and Wednesdays 12-3 am 
conceived by Bruno, Kavi, and Allen
produced by BL
January 30, 1996</h3></center>

<center><img src="/images/swmoon.gif" WIDTH = 174 HEIGHT = 240></center>



                    <img src="/images/swyinyang.gif" WIDTH = 30 HEIGHT = 31"><A HREF="#Bio">Bio</A>                                     <img src="/images/swyinyang.gif" WIDTH = 30 HEIGHT = 31 ><a href="/g/playlist.html">Playlist</a>

                    
                    <img src="/images/swyinyang.gif" WIDTH = 30 HEIGHT = 31 ><A HREF="mailto:bruno@quango.com">Feedback</A>                           <img src="/images/swyinyang.gif" WIDTH = 30 HEIGHT = 31 ><A HREF="#Our Picks">Our Picks</A>
                

                    <img src="/images/swyinyang.gif" WIDTH = 30 HEIGHT = 31 ><A HREF="/a/index.html">Take a look at us!</A>              <img src="/images/swyinyang.gif" WIDTH = 30 HEIGHT = 31 ><A HREF="/g/picks.html/#guez">Bruno's 10 X 5</A>


                    <img src="/images/swyinyang.gif" WIDTH = 30 HEIGHT = 31 ><A HREF="#Loo">Look out for...</A>                   <img src="/images/swyinyang.gif" WIDTH = 30 HEIGHT = 31 ><A HREF="#Rel">Related links</A>






<A NAME="Bio">
a Brief Biography of Bruno Haddad Guez - Host of Shortwave 

Music has always been an important part of Bruno Guez's life. 
  From as early as he can remember, Bruno has had an
 appreciation for good music- whether it was spending hours
 and hours going through his parent's extensive collection of
 Brazilian or European music from the 60's and 70's or the
 hands on experience of beating on an old African drum,  it was
 evident the music would continue to be an important part of his
 life.  

As a youngster, Bruno learned how to play the drums.  He quickly
 found that he had a good sense of rhythm and began experimenting
 with other forms of percussion instruments.  His DJ sensibilities 
were also evident from an early age - as a teenager he would mix 
his favorite rock tunes with a mixer and make compilation tapes as
 presents for his friends.  It wasn't  long before Bruno started
 experimenting with bolder and more adventurous mixes - mixing
 Led Zeppelin with Indian tablas or African beats with the Who didn't
 seem outrageous to Bruno.  

With such a colorful start in music, it is no surprise that Bruno 
chose to make a career in music.  His formal training came as a
 student of ethnomusicology at UCLA, but his true skills were
 demonstrated by his wide choice of music whenever he DJ's at
 events and clubs around Los Angeles.  

In the 80's, Bruno got his start at the pioneering West Hollywood
 nightclub Po Na Na Souk,  then a center for exotic music and styles.
  He would spend his days when the club was closed making tapes, 
learning about music and new sound sensibilities.  

Bruno began his radio career interning at KCRW's music library, 
eventually moving up to hosting his own show on Sundays from
 1-6 am.  Ever since it's first air date in  July  1993, to it's current
 form, Shortwave has evolved and continues to captivate those who 
know.   The program has been  very  experimental, incorporating 
acid jazz, trip hop, world beat, and ambient electric sounds into the
 late night air waves.  As each show progresses, the music pushes
 the boundaries of new electronica and international dance music.  

In 1995, Bruno and his partners developed Quango Music Group, an 
Island independent label primarily to  release domestic compilations
 and to introduce new European music that has been  over looked here
 in the states.   
     
          






<A NAME="Our Picks">
