<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=+3><B><TT>Commonly asked questions at KCRW</TT></B></FONT>
<P>

<DL>

<DD><B>How can I get in touch with National Public Radio?</B><P>


<DD>Address:    National Public Radio
<DD>635 Massachusettes Ave. NW
<DD>Washington D.C. 20001-3753
<P>

<DD>Phone numbers:

<DD>Audience Services for tapes & transcripts: 202-414-3232
<DD>Comment Line for Morning Edition: 202-842-5044
<DD>Comment Line for Weekend Edition Sunday: 202-371-1775
<P>
<DD>E-mail Address:  

<DD>Morning Edition: MORNING@NPR.ORG
<DD>All Things Considered: ATC@NPR.ORG
<DD>Weekend Edition Sunday: WESUN@NPR.ORG
<DD>Weekend All Things Considered: WATC@NPR.ORG

<P>
<B>What is the address and phone number of KCRW?  </B><P>

<DD>KCRW
<DD>1900 Pico Blvd.
<DD>Santa Monica, CA. 90405
<DD>Office #: 310-450-5183
<DD>Fax: 310-450-7172
<DD>E-mail: KCRWRADIO@AOL.COM
<P>
<B>How can I become a volunteer?</B><P>

<DD>If you would like information sent to you on how to become a volunteer for
KCRW, write to: 

<DD>Joshua Berman c/o KCRW, 1900 Pico Blvd., Santa Monica, Ca. 90405 and request 
volunteer information.

<P>
<B>Can I obtain a tape or playlist of a KCRW music program?
</B><P>
<DD>If you would like a playlist of a music program you heard on KCRW, we will
provide one to you at no cost.  Simply send us a self addressed, stamped envelope
to KCRW or call 310-450-5183 and request a playlist from one of our volunteers. 
Please include the date, time and title of the show you are requesting.

<DD>Neither the music programs nor the live performances /  interviews on them
are available on tapes.  However, Chris Douridas, host of KCRW's Morning Becomes
Eclectic, and Bob Carlson, KCRW's Production Director, have compiled and produced
two compact disks,  Rare On Air I & II, featuring music performed live on Morning
Becomes Eclectic.  Rare on Air II is available exclusively by becomming a KCRW
suscriber and Rare on Air I is currently available through local music retailers.
<P>
