your e-Mail to: <A HREF="mailto:mail@kcrw.org">mail@kcrw.org</A>.  
<P>
<B>How do I submit music to KCRW for airplay?</B>
<DD>KCRW considers all music for airplay.  CD's are preferable, but we accept
vynil, DAT and cassette.  Send your music, to: 
<P>
<DD>Chris Douridas, KCRW Music Director
<DD>c/o KCRW
<DD>1900 Pico Blvd.
<DD>Santa Monica, CA. 90405
<P>
<DD>To track the status of your submission, allow 2 to 3 weeks before you call.
Contact Gary Calamar, KCRW's Tracking Coordinator at 310-314-4640, Wednesday and
Thursday afternoons, from 1 - 3pm (Pacific Standard Time.)   
<P>
<DD>What if I want to submit a program or program idea to KCRW?
<P>
<DD>Please note that KCRW has a full program schedule and we rarely have open
slots for new programs. 
<P>
<DD>Send an audition cassette of your program, or a one page synopsis of your
idea, with a cover letter to:
<P>
        <DD>Auditions Department / Ruth Seymour
        <DD>KCRW
        <DD>1900 Pico Blvd
        <DD>Santa Monica, CA. 90405
<P>
<DD>All program submissions will be considered and responded to. Please remember
we are a small operation and some responses may take a while.
<P>

<B>How do I subscribe (donate money) to KCRW?   </B><P>

<DD>Our basic annual subscription rate is $25.  You can send your donation to:
<P>
<DD>KCRW Membership
<DD>1900 Pico Blvd.
<DD>Santa Monica, CA. 90405
<P>
<DD>Or call us at 310-450-5183 and we'll send you information on how to become a
subscriber.  
<P>
<B>Who do I contact if I'm interested in underwriting or developing corporate
support for KCRW Programming?  </B>
<P>
<DD>Contact Matt Holzman, KCRW Development Director at 310-314-4622.  


</DL>





