<TITLE>JEWISH SHORT STORIES</TITLE>





</HEAD> <BODY BACKGROUND="/images/bg-b.gif">

 
<BLOCKQUOTE>



<TT>
<A HREF="../images/jss.jpg"><IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="../images/jss.gif" BORDER=0

WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=137 HSPACE=20 VSPACE=10></A><B><FONT
SIZE=+4>JEWISH SHORT STORIES</FONT></B><BR>
<FONT SIZE = +1>FROM EASTERN EUROPE AND BEYOND</FONT></TT><P> 







<DL><IMG SRC="../images/nimoy.gif" ALT="Leonard Nimoy Recording"
WIDTH=191 HEIGHT=120 BORDER=2 ALIGN=right> 

<TT><B>Listen to stories from the series which captures

the vitality, humor and contradictions of modern Jewish life</B>



<P>



<B>

<A HREF="http://www.kcrw.org/ra/js_intro_n.ram"><IMG ALIGN=ABSMIDDLE
SRC="../images/ra2.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=5 WIDTH=25
HEIGHT=36></A><A HREF="http://www.kcrw.org/ra/js_intro.ram"><IMG
ALIGN=ABSMIDDLE SRC="../images/ra.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=10 VSPACE=5
WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36></A>INTRODUCTION by Leonard
Nimoy</BLOCKQUOTE>
 <BLOCKQUOTE>
 <A HREF="jss.html">LISTEN TO THE STORIES IN REAL AUDIO</A><BR>

<A HREF="jsscredits.html">ABOUT THE DIRECTOR AND PRODUCERS</A>

</B>

<P>

Purchase Jewish Short Stories on audio cassette.  The 9 cassette series is $100

which includes a one-year subscription to KCRW, and $80 for each
additional set. <A HREF="/cgi/s-filter.pl/b/s-form.html"><FONT SIZE = +2>Order
now.</FONT></A></B></TT>

<P>
<HR WIDTH = 20%>
<P>

The National Yiddish Book Center and <B>KCRW</B> 89.9FM/Santa Monica

announce the release of "Jewish Short Stories From Eastern Europe and Beyond," an

extraordinary new series from National Public Radio featuring stories of modern

Jewish

writers read by leading actors of stage and screen.  National Public Radio will

begin

distributing the thirteen-part series in July of 1995.

<P>

Hosted by Leonard Nimoy, the series captures the rich and diverse legacy of

modern Jewish

life through short stories by authors including Isaac Bashevis Singer, Cynthia

Ozick,

Isaac Babel, Grace Paley, I.L. Peretz and Philip Roth.

<P>

The stories are read by Walter Matthau, Lauren Bacall, Alan Alda, Eli Wallach,

Elliot

Gould, Claire Bloom, Jeff Goldblum, Carol Kane and other noted actors.  Directed

by Joan

Micklin Silver (Crossing Delancey, Hester Street), the series features original

music

composed and conducted by Hankus Netsky, founder of the acclaimed Klezmer

Conservatory

Band.

<P>

From a boisterous wedding thrown by a Jewish gangster in Odessa to an unorthodox

Christmas play in the Bronx, the stories range from the hilarious to the tragic,

capturing the humor, vitality, conflicts and contradictions of modern Jewish

life.  Each

of the one-hour programs includes an introduction highlighting central themes. 

The

series features translations of modern Jewish literature from Yiddish, Hebrew and

Russian, as well as American Jewish stories that reflect the wide range of

secular,

religious, political and cultural experiences of immigrant Jews from Russia,

Poland and

other countries.

<P>

Following NPR's national distribution, The National Yiddish Book Center, a 25,000

member

organization dedicated to the preservation and enhancement of Jewish culture,

will

produce and distribute a cassette version of the series along with supporting

educational

materials.

<P>

Major funding for "Jewish Short Stories From Eastern Europe and Beyond" was

provided by

the Joseph S. and Diane Steinberg Charitable Trust of New York City. Additional

support

was provided by the Nathan Cummings Foundation, the Dora Teitelboim Foundation,

the

California Arts Council, the Joseph Meyerhoff Memorial Trusts, Irving and Trude

Lehrer,

The National Endowment for the Arts, and the members and friends of <B>KCRW</B>

and the National

Yiddish Book Center.


