<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>MY STORY</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND = "../images/bg-bn.gif">

<B><FONT SIZE=+6>M</FONT></B><FONT SIZE= +1>Y STORY...
Hi, I'm Tricia Halloran, your host Monday through Wednesday,  from 10 to midnight on KCRW 89.9 FM in Los Angeles. When people ask me what kind of music I play, I say "alternative". It's not a great word, and it's been overused a lot, but I haven't found a better one yet. But what is alternative music, and why is my show called "Brave New World"?<P>


Well, in Shakespeare's play "The Tempest", a young girl who has lived her entire life on an isolated island suddenly encounters some fascinating strangers that will change her life forever. "Oh, Brave New World," she exclaims loudly, "that has such people in't!".<P>

That's exactly how I feel every day as I discover the music that jumps, kicks, whispers, and screams its way into your soul. Perhaps because I don't share my feelings all that easily, I am constantly amazed by artists who can bare their souls with a few well-written words and some musical notes. In so doing, they connect with listeners looking for a voice outside the mainstream, looking for an alternative.<P>

Alternative music can be world, punk, acoustic, country, dance, or rap. It can be on a major record label, an indie label, or even a self-produced cassette tape. Alternative music always captures the moment, the feel of the world or one person's world, right NOW.<P>
It's always moving forward and occasionally looking back. It usually has a melody, but not always. It's often loud, because it's about emotion, but it's often quiet for the same reason. It can be as well known as REM, or as little known as Anodyne.<P>

It's about substance over style, and following your heart.<P>

It gives you a choice, and makes you think about the choosing.</B>
<PRE>

</PRE>
