L.A. performance marks their California debut.  And they've been together33 years!</FONT></TT></B></TD> <TD><B><FONTSIZE=+1><TT>November 3, 1996</TT></FONT></B><TH><!--A HREF= "/ra/cl61103n.ram"--><IMG SRC="../images/ra2.gif" ALIGN = TEXTTOP BORDER=0 HSPACE=5 VSPACE=5 WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36><!--/A><A HREF = "/ra/cl61103.ram"--><IMG SRC="../images/ra.gif" ALIGN = TEXTTOP BORDER=0 HSPACE=5 VSPACE=5WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36><!--/A--></TH></TR><!--Row Ends Here--><!--Row Starts Here--><TR VALIGN = TOP><TD><B><TT><FONT SIZE=+1><BLINK>Coming soon!!</BLINK> Lokua Kanza is a young, gifted, Zairian musician who makes music that is not Zairian at all.  Hisvoice and melodies have captivated people both in Kinchasa, Paris and now here in America.  His new release, Wapi Tu, has just been released domestically on BMG.</FONT></TT></B></TD> <TD><B><FONTSIZE=+1><TT>August 27, 1996</TT></FONT></B><TH><A HREF= "/ra/cl61027n.ram"><IMG SRC="../images/ra2.gif" ALIGN = TEXTTOP BORDER=0 HSPACE=5 VSPACE=5 WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36></A><A HREF = "/ra/cl61027.ram"><IMG SRC="../images/ra.gif" ALIGN = TEXTTOP BORDER=0 HSPACE=5 VSPACE=5WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36></A></TH></TR><!--Row Ends Here--><!--Row Starts Here--><TR VALIGN = TOP><TD><B><TT><FONT SIZE=+1>Cesaria Evora is indisputably the most glorious diva to emerge on theinternational music scene.  Her recordings have captured huge audiences inFrance, America, and Brazil;  her dark &  rich voice,  and iconoclasticbehavior--like taking cigarette breaks on stage--have won her adoring fansworldwide.</FONT></TT></B></TD> <TD><B><FONTSIZE=+1><TT>August 12, 1996</TT></FONT></B><TH><A HREF= "/ra/cl61012n.ram"><IMG SRC="../images/ra2.gif" ALIGN = TEXTTOP BORDER=0 HSPACE=5 VSPACE=5 WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36></A><A HREF = "/ra/cl61012.ram"><IMG SRC="../images/ra.gif" ALIGN = TEXTTOP BORDER=0 HSPACE=5 VSPACE=5WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36></A></TH></TR><!--Row Ends Here--><!--Row Starts Here--><TR VALIGN = TOP><TD><B><TT><FONT SIZE=+1>Cuban music's latest and most fashionable mambo queen, Albita, stops in for an interview and live performanc.</FONT></TT></B></TD> <TD><B><FONTSIZE=+1><TT>September 28, 1996</TT></FONT></B><TH><A HREF= "/ra/cl60928n.ram"><IMG SRC="../images/ra2.gif" ALIGN = TEXTTOP BORDER=0 HSPACE=5 VSPACE=5 WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36></A><A HREF = "/ra/cl60928.ram"><IMG SRC="../images/ra.gif" ALIGN = TEXTTOP BORDER=0 HSPACE=5 VSPACE=5WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36></A></TH></TR><!--Row Ends Here--><!--Row Starts Here--><TR VALIGN = TOP><TD><B><TT><FONT SIZE=+1>Combining elements of jazz, blues, and alternative, Vanessa Daou hasemerged as one of the most musical and provocative vocalists on the popscene.</FONT></TT></B></TD> <TD><B><FONTSIZE=+1><TT>September 21, 1996</TT></FONT></B><TH><A HREF= "/ra/cl60921n.ram"><IMG SRC="../images/ra2.gif" ALIGN = TEXTTOP BORDER=0 HSPACE=5 VSPACE=5 WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36></A><A HREF = "/ra/cl60921.ram"><IMG SRC="../images/ra.gif" ALIGN = TEXTTOP BORDER=0 HSPACE=5 VSPACE=5WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=36></A></TH></TR><!--Row Ends Here--></TABLE><PRE><P><BR><BR><A HREF="cafela.html">Click here to return to Cafe LA Home page</A><BR><A HREF="live.html">Click here for more KCRW live performances and interview</A></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
