<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>About Tom</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<CENTER><H1>About Tom Schnabel</H1></CENTER>

<TABLE CELLSPACING=25 BORDER=0>
	<TR>
		<TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=CENTER><IMG SRC="../images/tom.gif"><P><H3>Tom Schnabel</H3><I><B>KCRW'S Host of<BR>Cafe L.A.</B></I></TD>
		<TD>Tom Schnabel attended USC, The Sorbonne, and UCLA, where he got a master's degree in comparative literature.  He later taught high school and college level English courses in Los Angeles, and later ESL in Paris.  An avid watersports enthusiast and Los Angeles Beach Lifeguard.  Tom found early on that the lifeguard tower was a perfect place to listen to music.  Later, he discovered Arab and African music while living in Paris.  Music has always been his passion. <BR><BR>Tom Schnabel has produced radio shows for radio station KCRW for 19 years.  During his tenure as Music Director (1979-90) KCRW went from an obscure college station to the biggest public station in the U.S.  He pioneered the use of the eclectic alternative format, introduced world music to public radio, and twice won the CMJ Best Noncommercial Station award (1986, 89).<BR><BR>
Schnabel left KCRW as Music Director in 1990 to renovate Horizon Records at A&M.  Unfortunately, Horizon Records fell victim to recession that hit the music industry in mid 1991.  Nevertheless, Schnabel continued producing programs for KCRW, teaching World Music and music appreciation courses at UCLA Extension, as well as producing World Music CD's:  (Trance Planet, 2 volumes, Worldly Music/Triloka) and Quango World:  Voices (Quango/Island).  Due in Fall, 1996, are Trance Planet Vol. 3, as well as Quango World:  Latin, a collection of great latin dance music.<BR><BR>
Schnabel is the author of many articles about music featured in the <I>Los Angeles Times</I>, <I>Jazz Magazine</I> (Paris), <I>Cashbox</I>, <I>Down Beat</I>, <I>Esquire</I>, <I>Buzz</I>, <I>LA Style</I> and a book, <I>Stolen Moments</I> (Acrobat Books).  A new book of interviews will be published in Spring, 1997, by Acrobat Books.</TD>
	</TR>
</TABLE>

<BR><BR>
