<A NAME = "guest"></A><CENTER>
<A HREF = "#top"><IMG SRC = "../images/hw.gif" BORDER = 0
HEIGHT = 96 WIDTH = 96></A>
<P>
<B>MORE ABOUT OUR GUEST</B>
<P>
<FONT SIZE =+2><B><TT>
<!--cci_show_guest-->
Alan Nierob<BR>Executive Vice President, Rogers & Cowan Inc.
<!--/cci_show_guest-->
</TT></B></FONT>
<P>
</CENTER>
<!--cci_guest_long_bio-->
Alan Nierob began his career at Rogers & Cowan Inc. in 1979
as an intern in the public relations company's Entertainment
Division. Several promotions later, he is now the Executive
Vice President of Rogers & Cowan's Entertainment Division.
<P>
Over the years, Mr. Nierob has worked with numerous actors,
actresses, personalities and sports stars, including Mel Gibson, Alec Baldwin,
Kim Basinger, Daryl Hannah, Ann-Margret, Victoria Principal,
Robert Wagner, Ali MacGraw, Bridget Fonda, Ray Liotta,
Dana Carvey, Danny Sullivan, Ozzie Smith and Giorgio Armani.
<P>
PR firms such as Rogers & Cowan handle campaigns for movie
and television actors, directors, producers and shows as
well as personal publicity for stars and personalities. They
assist a celebrity in managing his or her media coverage,
both good and bad, and often act as that star's link to
the outside world. The duties of a Hollywood publicist 
can include deciding which charities, personal appearances,
interviews and photos a celebrity will support or grant.
<P>
One of the biggest publicity companies in the world, Rogers
& Cowan's Hollywood office represents such A-list stars and
directors as Bruce Willis, Sylvester Stallone, Steve Martin,
and Robert Zemeckis. The company was founded by Warren Cowan
and Henry Rogers; it is now owned by a British conglomerate.

<!--/cci_guest_long_bio-->
