<P>

<FONT SIZE =+4><B><TT>
<!--cci_show_title-->
The Academy Awards<BR>Dishing The Dirt About Oscar!
<!--/cci_show_title-->
</TT></B></FONT>

<P>

<A HREF = "#guest"><B>GUEST</B></A>
<P>
<FONT SIZE =+2><B><TT>
<!--cci_show_guest-->
Frank H. Lieberman<BR>Senior Publicist<BR> The 68th Annual Academy Awards<BR> Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences
<!--/cci_show_guest-->
</TT></B></FONT>

<P>

<FONT>
<!--cci_guest_short_bio-->
The 68th Academy Awards will be held at the Dorothy Chandler
Pavilion of the Los Angeles Music Center on March 25, 1996.
The ceremonies, which are broadcast live around the world,
honor 1995 achievements in motion picture arts and sciences.
For this year's contest, a total of 225 feature-length films
met the general eligibility requirements for consideration.
Talents including Mel Gibson, John Travolta, Jim Carrey,
Martin Landau, Dianne Wiest, Anthony Hopkins, Tom Hanks,
Laurence Fishburne, Steven Spielberg, Robert Zemeckis, and
Jessica Lange are set to be Oscar presenters this year. 
<!--/cci_guest_short_bio-->
</FONT>
