"mailto:hollywood@kcrw.org"><B>Fan Mail</B></A> </CENTER>
<PRE>

</PRE><A HREF = "http://www.mckinley.com"><IMG SRC = "../images/3star44p.gif" BORDER = 0 HSPACE = 2 ALIGN = RIGHT WIDTH = 112 HEIGHT = 44></A>
<FONT SIZE = -1>HOLLYWOOD WRAP FEATURES THE NEWEST WORLD
WIDE WEB TECHNOLOGY.  YOU WILL GET THE MOST FROM THIS PAGE
WITH THE <A
HREF="http://home.netscape.com/comprod/mirror/index.html">NE
TSCAPE 2.0 BROWSER</A>, THE <A
HREF="http://www.realaudio.com/products/player/beta2.0form.h
tml">REAL AUDIO 2.0 PLAYER</A>, AND <A
HREF="http://www.macromedia.com/Tools/Shockwave/sdc/Plugin/i
ndex.htm">MACROMEDIA'S SHOCKWAVE</A>.</FONT>
<PRE>

</PRE>

<CENTER> <A HREF="../m.html"><IMG ALIGN=top
SRC="../images/kcrwww.gif"
WIDTH=144
HEIGHT=48 BORDER=0></A> </CENTER>

<PRE>









</PRE>
<A NAME = "guest"></A><CENTER>
<A HREF = "#top"><IMG SRC = "../images/hw.gif" BORDER = 0
HEIGHT = 96 WIDTH = 96></A>
<P>
<B>MORE ABOUT OUR GUEST</B>
<P>
<FONT SIZE =+2><B><TT>
<!--cci_show_guest-->
Frank H. Lieberman<BR>Senior Publicist<BR> The 68th Annual Academy Awards<BR> Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences
<!--/cci_show_guest-->
</TT></B></FONT>
<P>
</CENTER>
<!--cci_guest_long_bio-->
The 68th Academy Awards are presented by the Academy of
Motion Picture Arts and Sciences, whose purpose is to
recognize outstanding achievements in the arts and sciences
of motion pictures as a constant incentive within the
industry and to focus wide public attention upon the best
in motion pictures and to foster cooperation in the
creative leadership of the motion picture industry for
cultural, educational and technological progress.
<P>
Attendance at the annual Academy Awards is by invitation
only. No tickets are put on public sale.
<P> 
The first Academy Awards were handed out on May 16, 1929,
just as movies had begun to talk. The ceremony took place
at a banquet in the Blossom Room of the Hollywood Roosevelt
Hotel. About 250 people attended at a cost of $10 a ticket.
The early years of the awards had none of the suspense that
is their trademark today. Rather, results were given in
advance to the newspapers for publication at 11 p.m. on
the night of the awards, and the winners were all informed
ahead of time. But, by 1940, guests arriving for the awards
literally could buy the early edition of the newspaper and
learn the winners before the ceremony had even begun. Because
of that, the sealed envelope system was adopted in 1941 and
remains in use today.
<P>
For 15 years, the Academy Awards remained banquet affairs 
(the Ambassador Hotel and the Biltmore Hotel were also used
as venues).  But World War II, and increased attendance had
made the huge dinners impractical, so in 1942 the presentation
was made into a theatrical event. The 16th Awards were held
at Grauman's Chinese Theater and broadcast overseas to the
American GIs. After three years, the ceremony moved to the
Los Angeles Shrine Auditorium.During the war years, from
the 15th presentation through the 17th in 1994, plaster
statuettes were substituted for Oscars because of the shortage
of Britannia metal (an alloy of tin, copper, and antimony),
and copper-, nickel-, silver- and 24-karat gold-plating.
After the war, the plaster Oscars were replaced by metal ones.
<P>
The first televised Oscar ceremony was held at the RKO
Pantages Theater on March 19, 1953 by NBC-TV and radio
network with Bob Hope as master of ceremonies and Fredric
March making the presentations.On April 14, 1969, the
Academy Awards moved to the brand new Dorothy Chandler
Pavilion of the Los Angeles Music Center. Since then,
they have alternated venues with the Los Angeles Shrine
Auditorium.
<P>
There have only been three circumstances that have interrupted
the scheduled presentation of the Academy Awards. The first
was in 1938 when destructive floods all but washed out Los
Angeles. The ceremony was postponed in 1968 out of respect
for Dr. Martin Luther King who had been assassinated a
few days before the presentation an whose funeral was hel
on the day of the scheduled broadcast. And, in 1981, the
Awards were postponed for 24 hours due to the assassination
attempt on President Ronald Reagan.<P>
  
<!--/cci_guest_long_bio-->
